gomodel:SYNGO_393  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 1 Immunolabeling and confocal imaging of ephrinB3 shows that ephrinB3 is localized to mossy fiber axons and synaptic terminals in hippocampus of mice, specifically ephrin-B3-Beta-galactosidase fusion protein was colocalized with presynaptic marker synapsin 1 in stratum lucidum of CA3.\n\n23/6/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"triple-immunofluorescent labeling and confocal microscopy confirmed that immunoreactivity for ephrin-B3-β-galactosidase fusion protein (red) was not colocalized with the postsynaptic dendritic marker MAP2 (green) (e, f) but was colocalized with the presynaptic marker synapsin I (green)\"\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Hippocampal tissue was dissected from postnatal day 1 (PD1) mice" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_393" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

